## Violation C4: Missing Validation at the Data Bridge Level

**File:** [subtasks.repository.ts](file:///d:/Projects/sukoon/backend/src/modules/task/subtasks/subtasks.repository.ts#L31-L39)

```typescript
async updateSubTask(id: number, taskId: number, data: SubTasksType) {
    return await prisma.subTask.update({
        where: { id: id, taskId },
        data: data,   // ← Raw data passed directly to Prisma
    });
}
```

The repository accepts `SubTasksType` and passes it directly to Prisma. If `SubTasksType` includes unexpected fields (due to a bug or API change), Prisma might silently ignore them or worse, cause runtime errors. The repository layer — your "Data Bridge" — should validate or filter data before it reaches the database.

