## Violation I3: CRON Job Processes All Users Sequentially Without Locks

**File:** [cron.controller.ts](file:///d:/Projects/sukoon/backend/src/modules/cron/cron.controller.ts#L51-L66)

```typescript
const runPersonalizedQuranAya = async () => {
    const users = await authRepo.getAllUsers();  // ← Fetches ALL user IDs
    for (const user of users) {
        await personalizedAyaService.personalizedAyaWithAI(user.id);
    }
};
```

If this CRON endpoint is triggered twice (e.g., Railway sends a retry, or a health check re-fires it), both executions will:
1. Fetch the same list of users.
2. Process the same users in parallel.
3. Potentially create **duplicate personalized Ayas** for each user.

There's no **idempotency guard** — no check like "has this user already received their personalized Aya today before I generate a new one?"

